This code was written by Thomas Schoenemann, Petter Strandmark and Yubin Kuang
in 2009-2011. They are referred to as the "copyright holders" below. 

The code may be used, modified and distributed at the below given conditions.

To use this software, you need the following packages:

- Cbc http://www.coin-or.org/projects/Cbc.xml (tested with Version 2.4.0)
- GPC http://www.cs.man.ac.uk/~toby/alan/software/


Conditions for usage/modification/distribution: 

1. Usage is only allowed if it does not violate the LICENSE conditions
of either Clp or GPC. In case the license conditions of these
packages conflict with the ones given here, their rules have
precedence.  

2. The software is provided "as is" by the authors, with absolutely no
actual or implied warranty of correctness, fitness, intellectual
property ownership, or anything else whatsoever. You use the software
entirely at your own risk. In no event shall the copyright holder be
liable for any direct, indirect or perceived damage whatsoever
connected with the use of this work.

3. If you use this software for image SEGMENTATION, you are requested to cite
the paper

"T. Schoenemann, F. Kahl and D. Cremers - Curvature Regularity for
Region-based Image Segmentation and Inpainting: A linear programming
relaxation, ICCV 2009".

and, where appropriate 

"P. Strandmark and F. Kahl - Curvature Regularization for Curves and Surfaces
in a Global Optimization framework, EMMCVPR 2011"

in resulting publications. 

If you use message passing (MPLP,TRWS or Dual Decomposition), please cite 

"V. Kolmogorov and T. Schoenemann - Generalized Sequential Tree-reweighted
message passing", Arxiv Report, 2012.

If you are use QPBO, please also consider citing [EL Zehiry and Grady, CVPR 2010].


4. If you use this software for image INPAINTING, you are requested to
cite the more appropriate of the following papers:

- "T. Schoenemann, F. Kahl and D. Cremers - Curvature Regularity for
Region-based Image Segmentation and Inpainting: A linear programming
relaxation, ICCV 2009".

- "T. Schoenemann, Y. Kuang and F. Kahl - Curvature Regularity for Multi-Label
  Problems - Standard and Customized Linear Programming, EMMCVPR 2011".

5. Some included images are from the Berkeley segmentation database at 
http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Research/Projects/CS/vision/bsds/
Please cite 
@InProceedings{MartinFTM01,
  author = {D. Martin and C. Fowlkes and D. Tal and J. Malik},
  title = {A Database of Human Segmented Natural Images and its
           Application to Evaluating Segmentation Algorithms and
           Measuring Ecological Statistics},
  booktitle = {Proc. 8th Int'l Conf. Computer Vision},
  year = {2001},
  month = {July},
  volume = {2},
  pages = {416--423}
}
if those images are used.

6. Permission to use or distribute this software for commercial or
military purposes is NOT granted unless directly implied by the Clp
and/or GPC licenses.
